WEBVTT

00:00.864 --> 00:02.085
<i>Before there was sex,</i>

00:02.205 --> 00:05.076
<i>before there was the city,</i>
<i>there was just me,</i>

00:05.196 --> 00:08.431
<i>Carrie... Carrie Bradshaw</i>
<i>from Castlebury, Connecticut.</i>

00:08.433 --> 00:10.333
Last night, Harlan and I...

00:10.335 --> 00:11.934
<i>Harlan</i> Harlan?
My dad's friend Harlan?

00:11.936 --> 00:13.135
Yes. We're still together.

00:13.137 --> 00:14.837
I am so smitten with you,

00:14.839 --> 00:16.539
I wanted to go out of my way to see
your gorgeous face.

00:16.541 --> 00:17.673
Really,
I couldn't be happier

00:17.675 --> 00:18.841
that you got into Harvard.

00:18.843 --> 00:20.643
Do you not love me anymore?

00:20.645 --> 00:21.844
Maybe I'm just exhausted

00:21.846 --> 00:23.346
from your endless need
for competition.

00:23.348 --> 00:24.847
I've been wanting
to move to Laguna full-time.

00:24.849 --> 00:26.048
I don't know, dad.

00:26.050 --> 00:27.883
It's a done deal, Sebastian.
You're coming.

00:27.885 --> 00:29.418
We can make
long-distance work.

00:29.420 --> 00:32.822
I refuse to say "Good-bye"
because it's not good-bye.

00:32.942 --> 00:36.374
<font color="#3399FF">The Carrie Diaries 02x09</font>
<font color=#00ff00>Under Pressure</font>
Originally Aired January 3, 2014

00:36.494 --> 00:37.863
==sync, correction by <font color=#00ff00>dcdah</font>==
for www.addic7ed.com

00:39.464 --> 00:40.796
<i>It was a new year,</i>

00:40.798 --> 00:42.798
<i>and with a new year,</i>
<i>there comes new pressures...</i>

00:42.800 --> 00:46.769
<i>Like having my newly rekindled</i>
<i>love living 3,000 miles away.</i>

00:46.771 --> 00:51.073
<i>Hola!</i> Marisol, um,
is Sebastian there?

00:51.075 --> 00:53.108
Do you know when he'll be back?

00:53.110 --> 00:56.078
Okay. Thanks.

00:56.080 --> 00:57.846
<i>My long-distance relationship</i>

00:57.848 --> 01:00.349
<i>was definitely</i>
<i>not going gracefully.</i>

01:00.351 --> 01:02.117
Did Sebastian call?

01:02.119 --> 01:04.687
You just missed him.

01:04.688 --> 01:06.622
<i>It seemed like no matter how
hard we tried...</i>

01:06.624 --> 01:09.858
<i>to make
time for each other...</i>

01:09.860 --> 01:12.394
<i>Something would intervene.</i>

01:12.396 --> 01:14.163
Hello?

01:14.165 --> 01:15.497
Oh, it's you!

01:15.499 --> 01:17.132
It's really you.
I can't believe it.

01:17.134 --> 01:18.333
I know.
It was starting to seem

01:18.335 --> 01:19.968
like the world
didn't want us to talk.

01:19.970 --> 01:22.237
But the world did...
want us to talk.

01:22.239 --> 01:24.373
And... and here we are,
talking.

01:24.375 --> 01:26.575
- Pretty great.
- So great.

01:26.577 --> 01:29.478
So tell me everything.
What have you been up to?

01:29.480 --> 01:30.579
How is it with your dad?

01:30.581 --> 01:32.080
<i>Please deposit</i>

01:32.082 --> 01:33.482
<i>an additional 35 cents</i>

01:33.484 --> 01:35.851
<i>to continue</i>
<i>this long-distance call.</i>

01:35.853 --> 01:38.186
No problem, Mrs. Operator.

01:38.188 --> 01:41.189
I've got my change purse
right here.

01:41.191 --> 01:43.125
No. No, no, no.

01:43.127 --> 01:45.494
No.
<i>Your call will be disconnected</i>

01:45.496 --> 01:47.996
<i>if you don't deposit</i>
<i>an additional 35 cents.</i>

01:47.998 --> 01:50.665
- Carrie, do you have the money?
- I-I thought...

01:52.336 --> 01:53.802
Hello?!

01:53.804 --> 01:55.537
♪ Who can explain
the thunder and rain ♪

01:55.539 --> 01:57.139
<i>No.</i>

02:01.912 --> 02:03.345
<i>♪ Don't get me wrong ♪</i>

02:06.016 --> 02:08.083
Kinda have to get to my locker.

02:08.085 --> 02:10.384
Let me guess...
Nerdling needs to study

02:10.387 --> 02:11.720
on her lunch break.

02:11.722 --> 02:14.456
I don't have to study...

02:14.458 --> 02:16.925
At all.
I got into Harvard.

02:16.927 --> 02:18.059
Why so blue?

02:18.061 --> 02:19.494
Realizing your last
cute boyfriend was West

02:19.496 --> 02:20.862
and you blew that?

02:20.864 --> 02:24.632
I mean, sure, it feels weird
that we're not together,

02:24.634 --> 02:27.602
but it feels even weirder
to have gotten into Harvard.

02:27.604 --> 02:28.970
Why?

02:28.972 --> 02:31.539
I've been trying to get in
since I came out of the womb.

02:31.541 --> 02:32.907
And now I did.

02:32.909 --> 02:34.175
Suddenly I'm
a goal-less wonder.

02:34.177 --> 02:36.344
What am I supposed to do
till I attend in the fall?

02:36.346 --> 02:38.379
Kiss lots and lots
of cute boys.

02:38.381 --> 02:39.781
That's your job.

02:39.783 --> 02:40.882
Apparently one
I've done too well.

02:40.884 --> 02:42.216
I realized today that

02:42.218 --> 02:44.552
the well of eligible bachelors
in this school

02:44.554 --> 02:46.087
has run dry.

02:46.089 --> 02:49.123
There's no way
you've dated <i>everyone.</i>

02:49.125 --> 02:50.625
I have.

02:50.627 --> 02:52.727
What about David Leventhal?

02:52.729 --> 02:55.697
Or Kyle Newman?

02:55.699 --> 02:58.466
Quiz Bowl and Mathletes
over there do not count.

02:58.468 --> 03:00.301
By "eligible," I mean <i>hot.</i>

03:00.303 --> 03:02.470
And I've dated them all...
Even Walt, and he's gay.

03:02.472 --> 03:06.040
It's gonna be a long bust
of a spring semester.

03:06.042 --> 03:07.775
Look at us...

03:07.777 --> 03:09.877
Two girls with no purpose.

03:09.879 --> 03:11.012
Positively shocking to think

03:11.014 --> 03:12.213
I have something
in common with you.

03:12.215 --> 03:15.316
Tell me about it.

03:15.318 --> 03:17.618
Well, well, well.

03:17.620 --> 03:21.155
I spy with my little eye
something very interesting.

03:21.157 --> 03:23.924
I thought you said
you dated every eligible guy.

03:23.926 --> 03:26.794
It's Mini-Bradshaw.
Is she smiling?

03:28.598 --> 03:30.798
I've known her since she was 5.

03:30.800 --> 03:33.367
I don't think I've ever
seen her teeth before.

03:33.369 --> 03:36.070
Finally some titillating
boy intrigue.

03:36.072 --> 03:37.471
I'm going in for a closer look.

03:37.473 --> 03:39.907
Have fun with your books, nerd.

03:39.909 --> 03:41.675
I wish I could.

03:41.677 --> 03:45.346
I cannot believe you put an M-80
in Mr. London's mailbox.

03:45.348 --> 03:47.114
That must have been so awesome.

03:47.116 --> 03:49.416
It popped right off the post.
Went like...

03:49.418 --> 03:51.885
at least 10 feet in the air.
It was pretty rad.

03:51.887 --> 03:54.655
Totally rad.

03:54.657 --> 03:57.725
I gotta get going.
I'll catch you in chemistry?

03:57.727 --> 03:59.560
Not if I catch you first.

03:59.562 --> 04:03.964
I mean, uh... see ya.

04:04.966 --> 04:07.134
Someone looks flushed.

04:07.136 --> 04:09.403
So you got the hots
for scruffy, huh?

04:09.405 --> 04:11.338
No. Not really.

04:11.340 --> 04:12.906
I mean, maybe.

04:12.908 --> 04:14.308
Whatever.
So what if I do?

04:14.310 --> 04:15.642
Your sister would never
have the guts

04:15.644 --> 04:19.012
to chase a bad boy,
but... you're different.

04:19.014 --> 04:22.082
And since I'm feeling
oh, so generous,

04:22.084 --> 04:23.850
I'm gonna give you
some free advice.

04:23.852 --> 04:25.018
Who says I need advice?

04:25.020 --> 04:26.653
And why are you so invested
in my dating life?

04:26.655 --> 04:29.122
Wanted to see if my influence
was potent enough

04:29.124 --> 04:31.792
to help you get your man,
but...

04:31.794 --> 04:34.227
you're not interested.

04:34.229 --> 04:36.196
Wait.

04:36.198 --> 04:37.497
I'm interested.

04:37.499 --> 04:39.266
Well, you have two options.

04:39.268 --> 04:42.102
One... you could continue your sad
little hallway flirtation

04:42.104 --> 04:45.172
for another six months
and pray this goes somewhere.

04:45.174 --> 04:46.273
What's option two?

04:46.275 --> 04:48.108
Create a casual,
laid-back situation

04:48.110 --> 04:49.309
where you can get some time
with your boy

04:49.311 --> 04:51.645
outside of these
pathetic halls.

04:51.647 --> 04:55.815
- Like what?
- Hello? Like a <i>party.</i>

04:55.817 --> 04:57.517
He'll show up,
be drunk or stoned

04:57.519 --> 04:59.586
'cause that's what guys
like scruffy do,

04:59.588 --> 05:01.855
and you'll make your move.

05:01.857 --> 05:04.491
Is anybody having
a party this weekend?

05:04.493 --> 05:07.360
Not my problem.
I gave you the advice,

05:07.362 --> 05:09.663
you have to take it
from there.

05:09.665 --> 05:12.532
And please... don't disappoint.

05:12.534 --> 05:15.068
<i>Dorrit was suddenly
feeling the pressure</i>

05:15.070 --> 05:17.003
<i>to make something happen,</i>

05:17.005 --> 05:20.173
<i>while I was staring at</i>
<i>something created by pressure.</i>

05:20.175 --> 05:21.708
What is <i>that?</i>

05:21.710 --> 05:24.577
It's my gargantuanly
scrumptious engagement ring.

05:24.579 --> 05:25.979
You're engaged? To who?

05:25.981 --> 05:28.314
Darling, don't be daft.
To Harlan.

05:28.316 --> 05:31.184
<i>Oh.</i> I thought
that was just, like,

05:31.186 --> 05:33.753
- a sex thing.
- Mm, it is.

05:33.755 --> 05:36.022
But we're also in the throes
of a great love affair...

05:36.024 --> 05:38.925
he with me,
and me with this ring.

05:38.927 --> 05:40.293
Wait, so you don't love him?

05:40.295 --> 05:41.828
<i>J'adore</i> him.

05:41.830 --> 05:43.796
I just love the ring
one tick more.

05:43.798 --> 05:45.498
Well, I'm really happy for you.

05:45.500 --> 05:47.166
Sadly though, it means
my single life

05:47.168 --> 05:48.568
is now at a tragic end.

05:48.570 --> 05:50.470
I'll have to subsist
on tales of

05:50.472 --> 05:52.438
your deliciously
tawdry exploits now.

05:52.440 --> 05:54.273
- I'm sorry to disappoint.
- Oh, right.

05:54.275 --> 05:56.576
You don't have deliciously
tawdry exploits.

05:56.578 --> 05:59.112
What I meant is Sebastian
and I are still together.

05:59.114 --> 06:00.813
Well, in three months
when you are single,

06:00.815 --> 06:02.081
you'll have to dish.

06:02.083 --> 06:04.183
In three months I'll still
be dating Sebastian.

06:04.185 --> 06:06.152
I know long-distance
can be challenging.

06:06.154 --> 06:08.754
Sorry, but the moment
that taut, muscular goldilocks

06:08.756 --> 06:11.324
packed his bags,
that relationship was doomed.

06:11.326 --> 06:13.125
You're wrong about me
and Sebastian.

06:13.127 --> 06:13.708
We're gonna be...

06:13.828 --> 06:15.109
You're gonna be
the exception, yeah.

06:15.229 --> 06:16.329
That's what everyone says.

06:16.331 --> 06:17.563
But first it's
a few missed calls.

06:17.565 --> 06:19.165
Then it's a few
missed weekends.

06:19.167 --> 06:21.534
Then... you're not bothering
to call at all.

06:21.536 --> 06:23.235
Well, that's not gonna be us.

06:23.237 --> 06:26.072
Or worse...
one of you moves for the other.

06:26.074 --> 06:28.040
Why would that be worse?
That would be great.

06:28.042 --> 06:29.909
Mnh-mnh. Moving
puts way too much pressure

06:29.911 --> 06:30.910
on the relationship.

06:30.912 --> 06:32.778
After that, they start
resenting you

06:32.780 --> 06:34.747
for every little thing
that goes wrong.

06:34.749 --> 06:37.016
Ohh.
Next thing you know,

06:37.018 --> 06:38.951
you sleep with their brother,
and they're shouting at you,

06:38.953 --> 06:41.287
"I moved for you!
I moved for you!"

06:41.289 --> 06:44.690
Good God, man. Relax.

06:44.692 --> 06:46.692
Well, both of us are still
in high school,

06:46.694 --> 06:48.394
so I don't think
either one of us

06:48.396 --> 06:50.496
will be moving anywhere
for each other.

06:50.498 --> 06:54.433
So then it's the slow ride into
no relationship for you two.

06:54.435 --> 06:56.201
That's a shame.

06:57.371 --> 06:59.538
Girls!

06:59.540 --> 07:01.240
Come on down!

07:01.242 --> 07:04.042
What's up, dad?
This better be good.

07:04.044 --> 07:06.011
You interrupted me
doing nothing.

07:06.013 --> 07:08.347
Well, I won't keep you long.

07:08.349 --> 07:10.415
I know how much
doing nothing means to you.

07:10.417 --> 07:11.950
But I have been assigned

07:11.952 --> 07:14.553
to a highly confidential case
this weekend.

07:14.555 --> 07:15.988
I mean, Harlan won't give me
many details...

07:15.990 --> 07:18.891
that's how important it is...
but based on the secrecy,

07:18.893 --> 07:21.526
I am thinking
Fortune 500 merger.

07:21.528 --> 07:22.661
That's great.

07:22.663 --> 07:25.430
Yeah. I am officially
back with the big boys.

07:25.432 --> 07:26.865
Still wondering why I'm here.

07:26.867 --> 07:29.768
You are here because by being
put on this case,

07:29.770 --> 07:31.069
I'll be gone all weekend,

07:31.071 --> 07:32.771
which means I'll be leaving
you girls alone in the house

07:32.773 --> 07:34.139
tomorrow night.

07:36.976 --> 07:39.144
Now, Miss Meade
will be checking in,

07:39.146 --> 07:40.679
and I'll have my cell phone
with me, which means

07:40.681 --> 07:42.848
I'll be reachable at all times.

07:42.850 --> 07:44.683
This is a <i>test,</i>

07:44.685 --> 07:47.319
and I expect you to handle it
responsibly.

07:47.321 --> 07:49.354
If not, Miss Meade will be
right across the street

07:49.356 --> 07:50.355
to let me know.

07:50.357 --> 07:52.057
We can handle it, dad.
I promise.

07:52.059 --> 07:53.725
Brownnoser. I'd totally
have a party,

07:53.727 --> 07:55.594
but with Carrie here
to be my buzzkill,

07:55.596 --> 07:56.895
I'll just go to Audrey's.

07:56.897 --> 07:59.831
Fine. I'll probably
see a movie with Mouse.

07:59.833 --> 08:02.100
- Be home early.
- Fun.

08:02.102 --> 08:03.301
Sorry to miss it.

08:03.303 --> 08:05.670
Okay, good. Sounds like
this is gonna work out.

08:05.672 --> 08:07.639
But if you try to pull anything,

08:07.641 --> 08:09.974
- there will be hell to pay.
- Got it.

08:09.976 --> 08:11.509
Hear ya loud and clear.

08:11.511 --> 08:12.977
No funny business.

08:12.979 --> 08:14.712
Sebastian, my dad's
out of town this weekend.

08:14.714 --> 08:16.848
So get your butt
on the next plane.

08:16.850 --> 08:19.350
We have the whole house
to ourselves.

08:19.352 --> 08:22.053
Huge party at my house
tomorrow.

08:22.055 --> 08:25.089
Yeah, tell <i>everyone.</i>

08:27.000 --> 08:33.073
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

08:34.019 --> 08:35.150
- Hello?
- Hey, Mouse.

08:35.153 --> 08:36.852
Still up for seeing
"Out of Africa" tonight?

08:36.855 --> 08:38.520
Sebastian couldn't make it?

08:38.523 --> 08:39.822
When I finally
got in touch with him,

08:39.823 --> 08:41.357
he said he'd already
told Garret

08:41.359 --> 08:43.793
he'd go on a boating trip
with him this weekend.

08:43.794 --> 08:45.862
It <i>was</i> really short notice.

08:45.864 --> 08:48.831
I guess I just hoped he'd make
a huge romantic gesture

08:48.833 --> 08:51.334
and drop everything
to be with me.

08:51.336 --> 08:53.870
It's been almost a month
since we've seen each other.

08:53.872 --> 08:55.972
It's not like he lives
around the corner.

08:55.974 --> 08:58.341
- Laguna is far.
- I know.

08:58.343 --> 09:00.476
I just...

09:00.478 --> 09:02.745
Larissa kind of got in my head.

09:02.747 --> 09:04.714
Maybe she's right.
Maybe I'll never...

09:04.716 --> 09:06.515
see him again.

09:08.586 --> 09:11.587
That's probably Miss Meade
coming to check in on me.

09:11.589 --> 09:13.956
This is gonna be a fun day.

09:13.958 --> 09:15.958
I'll be right with you.
One sec.

09:17.461 --> 09:18.661
Miss me, Bradshaw?

09:18.663 --> 09:20.563
You came!

09:20.565 --> 09:21.664
Is that Sebastian?

09:21.666 --> 09:25.568
Yeah, bye.

09:25.570 --> 09:27.570
This is the best surprise ever.

09:27.572 --> 09:30.005
<i>And in that moment, I was sure</i>

09:30.007 --> 09:32.441
<i>Larissa knew nothing</i>
<i>about me and Sebastian</i>

09:32.443 --> 09:35.344
<i>and long-distance love.</i>

09:39.650 --> 09:41.283
Hey.

09:41.285 --> 09:42.484
Rager at my house tonight.

09:42.486 --> 09:45.020
- Sweet.
- You should come.

09:46.956 --> 09:49.291
You and your buddy, I mean.

09:49.293 --> 09:50.359
It's gonna be huge.

09:50.361 --> 09:52.961
- Awesome.
- We'll be there.

09:52.963 --> 09:55.130
Okay. Cool.

09:55.132 --> 09:58.667
<i>While Dorrit braced herself</i>
<i>for an exciting evening,</i>

09:58.669 --> 10:01.203
<i>my dad was about to walk into some
excitement of his own.</i>

10:01.205 --> 10:02.638
Hey.

10:02.640 --> 10:04.640
<i>Only, it wasn't the kind</i>
<i>he was expecting.</i>

10:04.642 --> 10:05.741
I'm glad you could make it.

10:05.743 --> 10:07.075
All right, so who's the client?

10:07.077 --> 10:09.177
M.C.I.? P&G?
One of the Ma Bells?

10:09.179 --> 10:11.213
- Me.
- Huh?

10:11.215 --> 10:14.883
<i>And...</i> me.

10:14.885 --> 10:18.253
I... I thought I was here
because of a big merger.

10:18.255 --> 10:19.488
Well, you are.

10:19.490 --> 10:21.723
One between me
and my Nubian Princess.

10:21.725 --> 10:25.627
I'm the princess, and I'm very Nubian.

10:25.629 --> 10:28.830
I'm leaving.

10:28.832 --> 10:31.933
I might be able to get home
in time to watch "Magnum, P.I."

10:31.935 --> 10:33.969
Wait, wait, wait,
wait, wait, wait, wait.

10:33.971 --> 10:35.103
Please.

10:35.105 --> 10:36.705
- You gotta do this.
- Do what?

10:36.707 --> 10:38.807
Help us bang out a prenuptial.

10:38.809 --> 10:40.876
I don't practice
that kind of law.

10:40.878 --> 10:43.278
You need a legitimate
unbiased family lawyer

10:43.280 --> 10:45.447
to mediate this.
Not me. Not a friend.

10:45.449 --> 10:48.650
No, Tommy, I need you
<i>because</i> you're my friend.

10:48.652 --> 10:51.753
Look, this woman...

10:51.755 --> 10:54.289
she is under my skin.

10:54.291 --> 10:55.590
I'm head over heels for her.

10:55.592 --> 10:57.659
If you're not here
to protect my interests,

10:57.661 --> 10:59.694
I might give up everything.

11:01.330 --> 11:02.797
Oh, come <i>on.</i>

11:02.799 --> 11:05.400
We'll order dinner in from...
Oh, Shun Lee.

11:05.402 --> 11:07.569
On me.

11:07.571 --> 11:10.238
You double my hourly rate,
you got a deal.

11:11.641 --> 11:13.441
Sold.

11:32.695 --> 11:35.062
I know I said
long-distance was fine,

11:35.064 --> 11:37.532
but honestly,
I missed you so much,

11:37.534 --> 11:40.268
I physically hurt.
I felt the same way.

11:40.270 --> 11:42.236
I didn't want to be
without you anymore.

11:44.873 --> 11:47.975
So your dad wasn't mad
that you missed your boat trip?

11:47.977 --> 11:49.710
No.

11:49.712 --> 11:51.779
He understood how much
I wanted to see you.

11:58.487 --> 12:00.755
How long do you think
you can stay?

12:00.757 --> 12:03.791
I'm not just here
for the weekend, Carrie.

12:03.793 --> 12:05.493
I'm here for good.

12:05.495 --> 12:07.161
I'm moving back.

12:09.364 --> 12:11.132
That's a good thing, right?

12:11.134 --> 12:15.069
Of course. No, that's a...
a great thing.

12:15.071 --> 12:17.171
It's just... wow. I...

12:17.173 --> 12:18.772
I wasn't expecting that.

