24:46.311 --> 24:49.079
Uh, that would just make things
worse for us.

24:49.081 --> 24:50.580
I-if we kick everyone out
like that,

24:50.582 --> 24:51.848
we'll be forever known
as the losers

24:51.850 --> 24:53.216
who couldn't handle
a fun party.

24:53.218 --> 24:56.152
Oh, you poor girls.
This is just awful.

24:56.154 --> 24:58.721
I feel for you.

24:58.723 --> 25:00.123
Oh, no.
Uh, Missus...

25:00.125 --> 25:01.724
Oh, it's Miss.

25:01.726 --> 25:04.060
I never married.
I wanted to.

25:04.062 --> 25:06.296
Never happened.

25:06.298 --> 25:08.064
Oh, I'm... I'm really sorry.

25:08.066 --> 25:09.399
That must be hard.

25:09.401 --> 25:10.600
It is.

25:10.602 --> 25:13.303
Thank you for being
so understanding.

25:13.305 --> 25:15.104
You're very nice girls.

25:15.106 --> 25:16.806
We try to be.

25:16.808 --> 25:17.974
And now...

25:17.976 --> 25:21.477
I'd like to help you.
Let me play the heavy.

25:21.479 --> 25:24.947
I'll clear these kids out,
one at a time,

25:24.949 --> 25:26.949
and you won't be to blame.

25:26.951 --> 25:29.786
Thank you... so much,
Miss Meade.

25:29.788 --> 25:31.521
You really get it.

25:31.523 --> 25:35.324
I do, don't I?
Now...

25:35.326 --> 25:37.126
Hey, you!

25:41.166 --> 25:43.099
Keep an eye on her.

25:45.103 --> 25:47.503
I cannot believe
she ate a whole brownie.

25:47.505 --> 25:48.804
She is gonna be down
for the count

25:48.806 --> 25:50.339
in about 20 minutes.

25:50.341 --> 25:52.375
Awesome!

25:52.377 --> 25:55.745
Um, do you wanna play
quarters or something?

25:55.747 --> 25:56.912
Cool.

25:56.914 --> 25:58.514
Give us a minute?

25:58.516 --> 25:59.915
<i>♪ Boy</i>

25:59.917 --> 26:03.019
uh, I'll go get some beers.

26:03.021 --> 26:05.688
I don't wanna ruin
what is clearly going well

26:05.690 --> 26:08.023
for you with cute and nice
over there,

26:08.025 --> 26:09.492
but I thought that
flock of seagulls boy

26:09.494 --> 26:12.761
with the grouchy attitude
was more your speed.

26:12.763 --> 26:13.829
He is.

26:13.831 --> 26:15.130
Scott's a friend.

26:15.132 --> 26:16.832
Oh, your boy didn't show, huh?

26:16.834 --> 26:18.033
No, he did.

26:18.035 --> 26:19.935
And you're wasting your time,
not to mention

26:19.937 --> 26:22.771
destroying your house,
so you can hang with a friend?

26:22.773 --> 26:25.241
Oh, you disappoint me.

26:25.243 --> 26:26.675
Have I taught you nothing?

26:26.677 --> 26:30.079
I'm taking my time.
Finding the right moment.

26:30.081 --> 26:31.614
People who wait
for the right moment

26:31.616 --> 26:33.615
end up waiting forever.

26:33.617 --> 26:35.150
With a party this crazy...

26:35.152 --> 26:37.853
Ain't gonna last
too much longer.

26:37.855 --> 26:40.456
I'm guessing the cops show
within the next hour.

26:40.458 --> 26:42.124
- So...
-  I'd get busy.

26:42.126 --> 26:43.392
On it.

26:43.394 --> 26:45.027
Make me proud.

26:45.029 --> 26:46.328
And when it's over,
I want details.

26:46.330 --> 26:48.330
I will be out back
playing beer pong with Mouse.

26:49.699 --> 26:50.966
I'm sorry, what?

26:50.968 --> 26:53.035
Don't ask.

26:53.037 --> 26:54.503
How'd you even know I was here?

26:54.505 --> 26:56.004
You're so uninterested
in my life,

26:56.006 --> 26:57.606
I'm surprised you knew
where to look.

26:57.608 --> 26:59.608
Your father filled me in
on everything.

26:59.610 --> 27:01.777
The two of you
have one little tiff,

27:01.779 --> 27:02.744
and you run away?

27:02.746 --> 27:04.413
You have to go back tomorrow.

27:04.415 --> 27:05.647
I'm not living
with him anymore.

27:05.649 --> 27:06.815
Not after what happened.

27:06.817 --> 27:07.883
Here we go!

27:07.885 --> 27:10.218
The two of you love drama,
don't you?

27:10.220 --> 27:12.421
It's why I couldn't
stay married to him.

27:12.423 --> 27:14.089
I can't do drama.

27:14.091 --> 27:15.490
I need a peaceful home.

27:15.492 --> 27:18.293
Which is why <i>you</i> cannot
come live with me.

27:18.295 --> 27:19.895
<i>That</i> was never the plan.

27:19.897 --> 27:22.430
You... you think I would ever
live with you

27:22.432 --> 27:24.432
and that boyfriend of yours?

27:24.434 --> 27:25.500
Husband!

27:25.502 --> 27:27.402
Lucas and I are <i>married.</i>

27:27.404 --> 27:28.770
Fine, mom.

27:28.772 --> 27:31.139
Either way, I was never
gonna live with you. Ever.

27:31.141 --> 27:33.475
So where exactly do you
think you'll be living?

27:33.477 --> 27:34.509
What are you gonna do?

27:34.511 --> 27:35.911
Move in with
your little girlfriend?

27:35.913 --> 27:38.413
It's none of your business.

27:38.415 --> 27:39.714
As usual.

27:39.716 --> 27:42.350
Just like your father,
you have no plan.

27:42.352 --> 27:44.919
Just flying by
the seat of your pants.

27:44.921 --> 27:46.621
Well, that isn't gonna
work for me.

27:46.623 --> 27:47.922
Come Sunday,

27:47.924 --> 27:50.425
you are getting on a plane
and going back to your dad.

27:50.427 --> 27:51.726
I will not.

27:51.728 --> 27:53.294
I'm 18 years old,
and you can't control

27:53.296 --> 27:54.596
what I choose to do anymore.

27:54.598 --> 27:56.831
And based on what a terrific
parent you've been,

27:56.833 --> 27:59.000
I don't see why I should
take orders from you.

27:59.002 --> 28:01.302
I'm done here.

28:03.340 --> 28:06.174
You're Carrie, right?
The girlfriend?

28:06.176 --> 28:07.208
Yeah.

28:07.210 --> 28:10.278
Well, good luck with him.

28:10.280 --> 28:12.447
He's all yours.

28:15.751 --> 28:17.819
<i>Suddenly,</i>
<i>I realized that Sebastian</i>

28:17.821 --> 28:19.687
<i>was a pressure cooker.</i>

28:19.689 --> 28:21.856
<i>I just hoped he wouldn't blow.</i>

28:21.858 --> 28:23.357
I'm gettin' it, dude!

28:23.359 --> 28:25.193
No, dude, dude,
you can't keep doing that.

28:25.195 --> 28:28.162
- No, man, hey, stop.
- You gotta let go.

28:28.164 --> 28:30.064
- You can't do that!
- Come on. Ohh!

28:30.066 --> 28:31.132
Oh, no!

28:31.134 --> 28:32.366
- Ohh!
- Aah!

28:38.808 --> 28:41.676
<i>Unfortunately,</i>
<i>something else did.</i>

28:45.833 --> 28:48.388
My dad's latest bimbo
hit on me.

28:48.508 --> 28:50.908
And yesterday, when I told him,

28:50.910 --> 28:52.943
she lied and said
I came on to her.

28:52.945 --> 28:55.412
Of course, Garret believes her

28:55.414 --> 28:57.248
because he's known her
for two whole minutes,

28:57.250 --> 28:59.650
and she's got fake double D's.

28:59.652 --> 29:01.452
I'm just his son.

29:01.454 --> 29:04.755
Why didn't you tell me
in the first place?

29:04.757 --> 29:06.123
That I'm an idiot?

29:06.125 --> 29:08.158
That I moved to Laguna
thinking I might

29:08.160 --> 29:11.628
actually have one parent
who cared about me?

29:11.630 --> 29:13.497
That doesn't make you an idiot.

29:15.101 --> 29:17.801
Sometimes I just wanna
kill Garret.

29:17.803 --> 29:20.504
Why does he keep
doing this to you?

29:20.506 --> 29:23.040
Because he's never
gonna change.

29:23.042 --> 29:25.175
That's why I had
to get out of there.

29:25.177 --> 29:29.413
The only place I wanted
to be was... with you.

29:32.250 --> 29:34.618
In a way, I'm relieved

29:34.620 --> 29:36.520
to know that you
didn't move back

29:36.522 --> 29:38.188
only because of me.

29:38.190 --> 29:42.726
That pressure freaked me out.

29:42.728 --> 29:44.928
I kinda sensed that.

29:44.930 --> 29:47.764
I'm not so good
at hiding my feelings.

29:47.766 --> 29:49.166
And you shouldn't.

29:49.168 --> 29:50.300
I always wanna know
what's going on

29:50.302 --> 29:51.568
in that head of yours.

29:51.570 --> 29:54.971
Even if it's hard for me
to say,

29:54.973 --> 29:57.407
or hard for you to hear?

29:57.409 --> 30:00.811
Even if.

30:05.716 --> 30:08.985
I feel like, every time
something goes wrong,

30:08.987 --> 30:10.720
I'm the person you lean on.

30:10.722 --> 30:13.790
And I'm glad that you
feel like you can.

30:13.792 --> 30:17.494
You always should
when you need to.

30:17.496 --> 30:20.030
But sometimes I feel like
that can be

30:20.032 --> 30:24.300
a lot for me, for us.

30:26.270 --> 30:29.539
I can't always put stuff aside
to be there for you.

30:29.541 --> 30:33.443
I know that,
and I don't want you to,

30:33.445 --> 30:35.311
especially on a night
like tonight,

30:35.313 --> 30:36.846
when you're dealing
with the party from hell.

30:37.816 --> 30:39.115
It really is, isn't it?

30:39.117 --> 30:43.119
Oh, this one is going down
in Castlebury history.

30:43.121 --> 30:44.520
That's what I was afraid of.

30:46.958 --> 30:48.057
I gotta go do something.

30:48.059 --> 30:49.826
Where you going?

30:50.828 --> 30:53.563
To take some of
the pressure off of you.

30:58.001 --> 31:01.504
Larissa, I have known you
to be an interesting,

31:01.506 --> 31:04.574
intelligent...
strange woman,

31:04.576 --> 31:06.952
who has had a wonderful
influence on my daughter,

31:07.072 --> 31:09.828
which is why this is all
so confusing for me.

31:09.948 --> 31:13.282
Isn't part of being married
about living with the person

31:13.284 --> 31:15.117
that you're going to
spend your life with?

31:15.119 --> 31:17.587
I mean, why won't you
move in with Harlan?

31:17.589 --> 31:20.523
I don't wanna live with him
because I'm afraid

31:20.525 --> 31:22.792
if I move in,
I'll become a person

31:22.794 --> 31:25.127
who has nothing
of herself left,

31:25.129 --> 31:26.329
and that scares me.

31:26.331 --> 31:27.563
Wait, but what do you mean?

31:27.565 --> 31:30.433
Moving in doesn't mean
you become less you.

31:30.435 --> 31:32.935
And yet it does.

31:32.937 --> 31:34.837
Because before long,
you dissolve

31:34.839 --> 31:36.972
into the relationship.

31:36.974 --> 31:39.141
First, you give up your place.

31:39.143 --> 31:41.844
Then you start
giving up your taste, hmm?

31:41.846 --> 31:47.449
Compromising on furniture,
clothes, where you eat.

31:47.451 --> 31:50.319
Then one day you're just
an appendage to someone else...

31:50.321 --> 31:52.555
No thoughts and no life
of your own.

31:54.324 --> 31:57.293
I feel like without a space
that is just mine,

31:57.295 --> 31:58.927
I'll disappear.

32:02.465 --> 32:03.966
Okay.

32:03.968 --> 32:05.834
Okay, then I think
I have a solution.

32:05.836 --> 32:07.636
All right? Harlan.

32:11.875 --> 32:14.243
Larissa is afraid...

32:14.245 --> 32:16.311
that if she moves in with you,

32:16.313 --> 32:20.582
she will lose everything
that makes her life special.

32:21.484 --> 32:24.219
Sweetie, I mean, I had no idea.

32:24.221 --> 32:25.787
I mean...

32:25.789 --> 32:30.158
I always want you to have
this big, spectacular life,

32:30.160 --> 32:32.461
right down to all those
knickknacks and tchotchkes

32:32.463 --> 32:34.029
you like to keep at your place.

32:34.031 --> 32:36.965
Good, then you won't mind
buying her her own apartment

32:36.967 --> 32:38.133
in your building.

32:41.571 --> 32:43.271
Seems like the perfect excuse

32:43.273 --> 32:45.140
to buy out my jerk
of a next door neighbor.

32:45.142 --> 32:48.577
I mean, we could even
put a-a door in to attach

32:48.579 --> 32:50.512
our two places.

32:50.514 --> 32:51.613
Baby, what do you say?

32:51.615 --> 32:53.849
I say give me the decorator
of my choice,

32:53.851 --> 32:56.384
with an unlimited budget,
and it sounds divine!

32:56.386 --> 32:58.153
All right, it's settled! Yes,
we figured it out!

33:00.557 --> 33:02.857
I am so happy to be
marrying you,

33:02.859 --> 33:04.226
my feral little minx.

33:04.228 --> 33:05.393
Mmm...

33:09.232 --> 33:10.732
I'm... I'm
a... I'm gonna be...

33:10.734 --> 33:12.067
going home now.

33:12.069 --> 33:15.070
Oh, nonsense!
It's 3:00 A.M.!

33:15.072 --> 33:17.639
You have your own suite
across the hall.

33:17.641 --> 33:20.742
Keys on the table,
room service on me.

33:20.744 --> 33:22.844
All right,
well, you two enjoy yourselves.

33:22.846 --> 33:24.979
I'm just... I'm gonna...
I'll be in my room,

33:24.981 --> 33:28.683
which is way over here,
way far, far away.

33:28.685 --> 33:29.784
You might still...

33:29.786 --> 33:30.919
Wanna find some earplugs.

33:30.921 --> 33:32.620
Oh!

33:32.622 --> 33:34.355
Aah!

33:36.960 --> 33:39.260
Hey, there you are.
I've been looking for ya.

33:39.262 --> 33:41.930
You wanna play quarters?

33:43.433 --> 33:45.933
I've got a better idea.

34:02.151 --> 34:03.451
Cops are coming!

34:03.453 --> 34:05.119
- Everybody run!
-  What?

34:05.121 --> 34:06.254
Everybody run!

34:06.256 --> 34:08.723
Get out of here!
They're gonna bust us!

34:08.725 --> 34:09.790
Get out of here!

34:09.792 --> 34:12.426
Come on, get out
while you still can! Run!

34:14.197 --> 34:15.563
I guess I should go.

34:15.565 --> 34:17.531
No, you don't.
You're coming with me.

34:17.533 --> 34:19.467
Come on, people! Go!

34:20.536 --> 34:22.003
Now the cops are coming?

34:22.005 --> 34:24.505
Perfect. My dad is going
to murder us.

34:24.507 --> 34:25.906
No cops. I made it up.

34:25.908 --> 34:28.809
Oh, thank you.

34:31.313 --> 34:32.780
I believe these are yours.

34:32.782 --> 34:37.751
I love these sunglasses.

34:44.460 --> 34:46.092
So what should we do now?

34:46.094 --> 34:48.661
Well, we don't have
to do anything.

34:48.664 --> 34:51.065
We can clean this all up later.

34:51.067 --> 34:53.734
Well, since we're not
cleaning up until later,

34:53.735 --> 34:56.704
I have a couple thoughts on what
we <i>could</i> do right now.

34:56.706 --> 34:58.672
Oh, you do?

34:59.574 --> 35:02.209
Come on, Kydd.
Let's go upstairs.

35:02.211 --> 35:04.478
Oh, right this second?

35:04.480 --> 35:06.046
Look who's putting
the pressure on now.

35:06.048 --> 35:08.715
I think you can handle it.

35:20.075 --> 35:25.245
<i>The morning after</i>
<i>a big bash can be exciting...</i>

35:28.015 --> 35:31.217
<i>or surprising.</i>

35:32.853 --> 35:34.454
What's the rush?

35:34.456 --> 35:35.855
Oh, I gotta go.

35:35.857 --> 35:38.491
If my girlfriend finds out,
she'll totally dump me.

35:38.493 --> 35:41.127
You have a girlfriend?

35:41.129 --> 35:42.862
Yeah. I thought you knew.

35:42.864 --> 35:44.697
I did not.

35:44.699 --> 35:45.932
Oh.

35:45.934 --> 35:47.500
You're such a jerk.

35:47.502 --> 35:49.736
Get the hell outta here.

35:54.675 --> 35:59.512
<i>It can also create</i>
<i>strange bedfellows.</i>

36:07.087 --> 36:08.254
This never happened.

36:08.256 --> 36:10.356
Agreed.

36:10.358 --> 36:13.226
But you're kind of
a good snuggler.

36:13.228 --> 36:15.628
You, too.

36:22.537 --> 36:24.770
I was wondering where you were.

36:24.772 --> 36:26.806
Just figured I'd get
a jump start on the day,

36:26.808 --> 36:29.842
clean up, take some things
off your plate.

36:29.844 --> 36:31.777
I made some coffee.

36:31.779 --> 36:34.513
Thank you.

36:34.515 --> 36:36.282
I also called my dad
this morning.

36:36.284 --> 36:37.483
We talked it out.

36:37.485 --> 36:39.952
Okay. Are you going back?

36:39.954 --> 36:42.121
No,
we both agreed that our relationship

36:42.123 --> 36:44.123
probably works better
long distance.

36:44.125 --> 36:46.659
He's gonna give me an allowance

36:46.661 --> 36:48.093
to find a place in Manhattan,

36:48.095 --> 36:49.128
so I can put down roots.

36:49.130 --> 36:51.530
That's so great! Yay!

36:51.532 --> 36:53.799
Carrie, that was dad
on the phone.

36:53.801 --> 36:55.201
He's coming back in an hour.

37:05.111 --> 37:06.478
We've got work to do.

37:06.480 --> 37:08.881
Well, fun party,
but I'm outta here.

37:09.949 --> 37:12.418
<i>Pressure can take us</i>
<i>to some messy places.</i>

37:12.420 --> 37:15.054
<i>If we bottle it up,</i>
<i>it can explode.</i>

37:15.056 --> 37:19.825
♪ Last night a little dancer,
she came dancin' to my door ♪

37:19.827 --> 37:21.894
<i>If we only try to alleviate it,</i>

37:21.896 --> 37:24.496
<i>it can lead us</i>
<i>to make very bad decisions.</i>

37:24.498 --> 37:26.431
♪ On the floor

37:26.433 --> 37:27.699
♪ she said...

37:27.701 --> 37:30.135
<i>But sometimes</i>
<i>the force created by pressure</i>

37:30.137 --> 37:32.738
<i>pushes us to a place</i>
<i>where we have to get through</i>

37:32.740 --> 37:33.906
<i>something together.</i>

37:33.908 --> 37:36.742
♪ pray help from above

37:36.744 --> 37:38.176
<i>and often...</i>

37:38.178 --> 37:39.278
♪ Because in the midnight hour

37:39.280 --> 37:41.079
<i>that's when we're at our best.</i>

37:41.081 --> 37:43.782
♪ She cried more, more, more

37:43.784 --> 37:46.852
♪ with a rebel yell

37:46.854 --> 37:48.720
♪ more, more, more

37:48.722 --> 37:50.155
♪ more, more, more

37:50.157 --> 37:53.959
fun night?

37:53.961 --> 37:55.360
Interesting.

37:55.362 --> 37:56.795
Turns out getting into Harvard

37:56.797 --> 37:59.431
got me into some other
weird places.

37:59.433 --> 38:02.467
- I accidentally slept with Donna.
- What?

38:02.469 --> 38:04.836
Relax. We just spooned.

38:09.575 --> 38:11.409
I already tossed
most of the garbage

38:11.411 --> 38:12.344
in the town dumpster.

38:12.346 --> 38:13.545
I'm gonna go return the kegs.

38:13.547 --> 38:14.646
See you later?

38:14.648 --> 38:16.247
You bet.

38:24.256 --> 38:25.423
Girls?

38:27.561 --> 38:29.461
You here?

38:29.463 --> 38:30.528
Hey.

38:30.530 --> 38:32.597
Ah.

38:32.599 --> 38:34.232
How was your night?

38:34.234 --> 38:36.935
Uh, it was, you know,
pretty boring.

38:36.937 --> 38:39.170
Yep. Nothing much
to talk about.

38:39.172 --> 38:40.939
I'm relieved.

38:40.941 --> 38:42.006
I was worried I'd come home

38:42.008 --> 38:43.174
and the house
would be destroyed.

38:44.778 --> 38:47.011
I can't believe you would
think that of us, dad.

38:47.013 --> 38:48.947
Really, I'm insulted.

38:56.488 --> 38:57.889
Girls?

38:57.891 --> 38:59.490
Hi, Tom.

39:03.762 --> 39:06.397
The woman just fell
out of the cupboard?

39:06.399 --> 39:07.865
What did you tell your dad?

39:07.867 --> 39:09.267
Well, Miss Meade
was so embarrassed

39:09.269 --> 39:10.968
that she lied and told my dad

39:10.970 --> 39:13.638
she must've sleepwalked
over to our place.

39:13.640 --> 39:14.972
We did leave her
with a spare key.

39:14.974 --> 39:18.042
Which he took back that day.

39:18.044 --> 39:20.378
So... what do you think
about the flat?

39:20.380 --> 39:21.579
I do hope you'll take it.

39:21.581 --> 39:24.582
I dread the thought
of strangers in my space.

39:24.584 --> 39:27.218
It's a bummer
you have to give it up.

39:27.220 --> 39:29.320
Darling, I'm not.
I'm subletting it,

